Eb wrote:
&gt;
&gt; &gt; What you&#39;re suggesting doesn&#39;t apply the hypertext constraint, it
&gt; &gt; relies on out-of-band information to create a function in client
&gt; &gt; chrome, a definite coupling compared to hypertext-driven DELETE.
&gt; &gt;
&gt; And why is it that the Xforms solution doesn&#39;t?  How does my machine
&gt; client know that a DELETE button has a certain meaning?  Is it just
&gt; implied because the word DELETE is used?  I&#39;m a little confused there.
&gt; 

A machine client could care less if the button is labeled &quot;foo&quot;.  It
just has to introspect the Xforms &quot;Model&quot; markup, typically located in
the document &lt;head&gt;, to understand exactly what happens when that
button is pushed -- one or more resources in a defined collection has
its DELETE method individually called in sequence.  It&#39;s a self-
documenting API that&#39;s easy for a machine client to interpret.

-Eric
